## Installation

1. Clone the repository.
2. Install the dependencies by running the following command

npm install

## Usage

- To start the project in development mode, run:

npm run dev


- To start the project in production mode, run:

npm run start


## Dependencies

- [express](https://www.npmjs.com/package/express) - ^4.18.2
- [dotenv](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv) - ^16.3.1
- [morgan](https://www.npmjs.com/package/morgan) - ^1.10.0
- [pg](https://www.npmjs.com/package/pg) - ^8.4.0
- [reflect-metadata](https://www.npmjs.com/package/reflect-metadata) - ^0.1.13
- [typeorm](https://www.npmjs.com/package/typeorm) - 0.3.17
- [uuid](https://www.npmjs.com/package/uuid) - ^9.0.1

## Scripts

- `start`: Transpiles the TypeScript code and starts the server using `ts-node`.
- `dev`: Starts the server in development mode using `ts-node`.
- `start:dev`: Starts the server in development mode using `nodemon`.
- `build`: Transpiles the TypeScript code to JavaScript.

